Večino piškotkov predstavljajo sejni piškotki, ki se samodejno izbrišejo z vašega trdega diska, ko zaključite svojo sejo (ko se odjavite ali zaprete svoj spletni brskalnik). Nekateri piškotki spletnim mestom omogočajo, da vas ob vrnitvi prepoznajo. Če takega piškotka ni, vas bodo spletna mesta, ki jih redno obiskujete (na primer <<BRAND>>), vsakič obravnavale kot novega obiskovalca. Piškotke je treba izbrisati le, če prejmete obvestilo, da vaš brskalnik zavrača piškotke.
Prepričajte se, da so v vašem spletnem brskalniku omogočeni piškotki.

Piškotki so majhne datoteke, shranjene na trdem disku vašega računalnika, ki so v pomoč pri omogočanju naših storitev. Tudi prijava na spletno stran <<BRAND>> deluje ob podpori piškotkov.

Ali se moram registrirati, če želim uporabljati <>?
Ne. Po spletnem mestu lahko brskate in v razdelku »Mali oglasi« objavljate oglase, ne da bi se registrirali. Registracija je potrebna, če želite objaviti oglas vrste »Kupi zdaj« ali po sistemu dražbe. Registracija na spletni strani <> je BREZPLAČNA, sam postopek pa zelo enostaven:

Katere vrste oblik nakupov in prodaj ponuja <>?
Oblike nakupov in prodaj, ki jih ponuja <>, kupcem in prodajalcem lajšajo medsebojne transakcije. Vsaka oblika ima svoje značilnosti in prednosti.

1. Mali oglas: pri tej obliki oglasa se lahko kupci vedno pogajajo s prodajalcem o ceni, čeprav je prodajalec objavil ceno predmeta.

2. Kupi zdaj: to je transakcija z nespremenljivo ceno, kjer mora uporabnik predmet prodati prvemu kupcu, ki je pripravljen plačati ceno, določeno s strani prodajalca.

3. Dražba: pri tej obliki mora prodajalec predmet prodati tistemu ponudniku, ki ponudi najvišjo ceno. Nazaj na vrh

Kako lahko na spletni strani <> najdem predmet?
Ko niste prepričani, kaj iščete, ali ko želite raziskati oglase na spletni strani <> ali v določeni kategoriji, lahko brskate po oglasih. Kliknite »Kategorije« in »Podkategorije« in če najdete predmet, ki vas zanima, enostavno kliknite naziv predmeta.

Iščete lahko tudi izbrane predmete, ki jih lahko opišete z nekaj besedami. Besede, ki opisujejo iskani predmet, vpišite v iskalno okno in kliknite gumb »Iskanje«. Prikazana bo stran z rezultati ustreznih objav na spletni strani <>. Preglejte rezultate iskanja in če najdete predmet, ki vas zanima, enostavno kliknite naziv predmeta. Nazaj na vrh

»<>« vam z enega varnega mesta omogoča sledenje in upravljanje nakupov, prodaj, objav, osebnega računa, informacij, sporočil, priljubljenih in še več na strani <>. Dostop do večine funkcij, ki jih omogoča <> , je na voljo le registriranim uporabnikom. Nazaj na vrh

Kaj počnejo prodajalci, ki so verjetno goljufivi?

  • Želijo, da jim nakažete denar na mednarodni račun. Prodajalec lahko zahteva, da mu nakažete denar v tujino in sprejema le Western Union ali drugo storitev pošiljanja denarja (e-Gold).
  • Navedejo naslov, ki se razlikuje od naslova, objavljenega na strani, kjer so podrobnosti o predmetu.
  • Priporočajo nepoznano storitev deponiranja ali plačilno storitev.
  • Niso odkriti o avtentičnosti predmetov za prodajo.
  • Ne posredujejo vam telefonske številke, ki bi jo lahko preverili.
  • Poskušajo vas prepričati, da ne bi uporabili plačilnih storitev, ki nudijo zaščito (sprejemljive storitve so npr. Escrow.com, PayPal in podobne).
  • Pogosto ne odgovarjajo telefonskim klicem in e-poštnim sporočilom.
  • Pogosto navajajo izgovore, zakaj še niste prejeli predmeta.
  • Prodajajo sumljive kopije programske opreme, glasbe ali videoposnetkov.
  • Ne želijo sporočiti številke pošiljke, ki omogoča njeno sledljivost.
  • Prodajajo drag, priljubljen predmet po sumljivo nizki ceni.
Nazaj na vrh


Kaj lahko storim, če sumim, da je prodajalec goljufiv?
Če menite, da je na spletni strani objavljen lažniv ali goljufiv oglas, nam pišite na naslov abuse@OLX.com. Nazaj na vrh


Kako se lahko goljufiji izognem?
V podjetju <> menimo, da je najzanesljivejše in najvarneje kupovati predmete lokalno, kjer lahko predmet preverite, spoznate prodajalca in plačate ob prevzemu ali dobavi. Pri nakupih znotraj države ali pri mednarodnih nakupih priporočamo, da se zavarujete pred goljufivimi prodajalci s pomočjo naslednjih ukrepov: Nazaj na vrh

  • Vedno uporabljajte sistem <>
    • Za stik s prodajalcem vedno uporabljajte povezavo »Stopi v stik s prodajalcem«, ki se nahaja na strani, kjer so navedene podrobnosti o predmetu. Na ta način boste poslali sporočilo prodajalcu, kjer bo navedena tudi vaša e-pošta in vse transakcije med vami in prodajalcem bodo izvršene neposredno preko našega sistema. Če smo obveščeni o goljufivi dejavnosti tega uporabnika, bomo imeli vaše podatke za stik in vas lahko o tem obvestimo. Ker je naše tržišče brezplačno, ne bi smeli imeti veliko razlogov za prenos komunikacije izven spletne strani.

  • Prepričajte se o predmetu nakupa
    • Preden prodajalcu pošljete svojo ponudbo, postavite vprašanja in pridobite podrobne informacije o predmetu, ki ga prodaja. Prodajalcu lahko pošljete sporočilo pred prodajo in oddate ponudbo, ko ste pripravljeni na nakup. Priporočamo tudi, da preverite maloprodajne cene in cene pri drugih uporabnikih ter si tako ustvarite primerjavo. Zapomnite si: če je cena videti predobra, da bi bila resnična, verjetno je. Če kliknete na "Izberi slike", se bo pojavilo okno, ki vam bo omogočilo izbiranje datotek z vašega računalnika. izberite slikovno datoteko, ki jo želite naložiti, in kliknite na "OK". Slika, ki jo postavite na prvo mesto, bo glavna slika vašega oglasa in se bo pojavila poleg naslova na seznamu kategorij. <<BRAND>> postopek nalaganja slik je enostaven, naložite pa lahko do 20 (dvajset) slik na oglas. Pri oglasih tipa malega oglasa bodo kupci vedno stopili v stik s prodajalcem za pogajanje, tudi če je prodajalec navedel ceno.
Kaj so stvari, ki jih naredijo kupci, ki so morda goljufivi?

• Prosijo vas, da jim denar nakažete na račun.
  • Kupec v zameno za predmet, ki je naprodaj, ponudi bančni ček visoke vrednosti (vendar ponarejen). Vrednost bančnega čeka pogosto veliko presega ceno vašega predmeta in kupec vas prosi, da mu razliko nakažete preko storitev za nakazila denarja. Banke pogosto izplačajo te ponarejene čeke, vendar ste potem VI ODGOVORNI, KO ČEKA NI MOGOČE POTRDITI. Prevara pogosto vključuje tretjo stranko (špediter, poslovni partner, ki kupcu dolguje denar). Močno vam odsvetujemo, da bi nakazali denar.
  • Priporočijo neznano depozitno ali plačilno službo.
  • Dajo velika naročila, ki naj bi jih poslali v tujino.
  • Pravijo, da vam bodo polovico zneska, ki vam ga dolgujejo, plačali pred dostavo in drugo polovico po dostavi..
  • Vam ne dajo telefonske številke, ki bi jo lahko preverili.
  • Plačajo z mednarodno kreditno kartico ali bančnim čekom.
Kaj so stvari, ki jih naredijo prodajalci, ki so morda goljufivi?

• Vas prosijo, da jim denar nakažete na mednarodni račun. Prodajalec vas morda prosi, da pošljete denar v tujino, in sprejema samo plačila preko Western Union ali drugih služb za nakazila denarja (e-Gold).
  • Navedejo naslov, ki je drugačen od naslova na strani o podrobnostih predmeta.
  • Priporočijo neznano depozitno ali plačilno službo.
  • Niso odkriti o avtentičnosti predmetov naprodaj.
  • Vam ne dajo telefonske številke, ki bi jo lahko preverili.
  • Vas poskusijo prepričati, da naj ne uporabite plačilne službe, ki nudi zaščito (odobrene so službe kot Escrow.com in PayPal).
  • Znova in znova ne odgovarjajo na telefonske klice ali elektronsko pošto.
  • Nenehno imajo izgovore, zakaj predmeta niste prejeli.
  • Prodajajo sumljive kopije programske opreme, glasbe ali videov.
  • Branijo se, da bi vam dali številko za sleditev pošiljki.
  • Prodajajo drag, popularen predmet po sumljivo nizki ceni.

Opomnik vas povpraša po  ključnih besedah/stavkih za predmete, ki vas zanimajo. Vsakič, ko je objavljen oglas s to ključno besedo / tem ključnim stavkom, boste prejeli e-pošto, ki vas bo obvestila o objavi. Potem si lahko objavo pogledate, če to želite. What is the Auction listing type?
What is the Buy Now listing type?

In the Buy Now-style listings, sellers have the option to offer a Buy Now price that allows a buyer to get the item right away. It is a fixed price transaction and the seller must sell the item to the interested buyer at the specified Buy Now price.
What is the Classifieds listing type?
In the Classifieds-style listings, buyers will always contact the seller to negotiate, even if he/she puts a price.

New to askht.com


What is askht.com?
askht.com is the world's online marketplace for local buying, and selling, exchanging and communicating to other users. Back to top

Is askht.com FREE?
Yes, askht.com is 100% free! Back to top

Do I have to Register to use askht.com?
No. You can browse the site and post items in the Classified section without registration. Registration is necessary in order to post a buy now or auction type of ad you. Registration at askht.com is FREE and the process is very simple:

1. Click on "Register Now" and you will be asked to provide your basic contact information.
2. You are now Registered at askht.com!
3. askht.com will send a message with your login and password information to your e-mail address.

Once you have registered, you can manage your postings and personal information even easier through the 'My askht.com' section of the site. Back to top

What type of buying and selling formats does askht.com offer?
askht.com buying and selling formats make it easy for buyers and sellers to do transactions together. Each format has its own characteristics and advantages.

1. Classified: Under this format, buyers can always contact the seller to negotiate, even if he or she puts a price to the item.

2. Buy Now: This is a price fixed transaction, where the user must sell the item to the first interested buyer at the stated price.

3. Auction: Rated auction, where the seller must sell the item to the highest bidder. Back to top

How do I find an item at askht.com ?

What is the Reserve Price?
Reserve price is the minimum price a seller is willing to accept for an item. The seller has no obligation to sell the item if the reserve price is not met. The buyer is not shown the reserve price, but only showed whether or not the reserve has been met. A winning bidder must meet or exceed the reserve price and must also have the highest bid. More Guidelines


What are the things that potentially fraudulent sellers do?

  • Ask you to wire money into on International account. Seller may ask you to send payment overseas and will only accept Western Union or another money transfer service (e-Gold).
  • List an address that is different from the address on their item detail page.
  • Recommend an unfamiliar escrow or payment service.
  • Not be up front about the authenticity of items for sale.
  • Will not provide you a verifiable telephone number.
  • Try to convince you not to use payment services which offer protection (accepted services are those like Escrow.com & PayPal).
  • Will repeatedly not answer phone calls or email.
  • Continuously provide excuses about why you haven't received an item.
  • Sell suspect copies of software, music, or videos.
  • Refuse to give you a working shipment tracking number.
  • Sell an expensive popular item at a suspiciously low price.
Back to top


What should I do if I suspect a fraudulent seller?
If you feel there is a posting on the site that is false or fraudulent, please contact us at abuse@OLX.com. Back to top


How can I avoid a fraud?
At askht.com, we believe that buying items locally - where you can inspect the item, meet the seller and pay at the time of pickup or delivery -- is the surest and safest way to transact. For National or International items, we strongly suggest taking the following measures to protect yourself from fraudulent sellers: Back to top

  • Use always askht.com system
    • When communicating with sellers on askht.com always do it using the "Contact Seller" link on the page that details the item. An email will be sent out to the seller with your email address and all transactions will be conducted between you and the seller directly via our system. This way, if we are notified of a seller's fraudulent activity, we will have your contact information to reach you and provide you with the information. Since our marketplace is always free, there should be little incentive to take communications off line.

  • Know what you are buying
    • Before making an offer to a seller, ask questions to learn more about what they are selling. You can send a seller a pre-sale note, and then make your offer when you are comfortable with purchasing the item. We also recommend checking retail prices and other members' prices for comparison purposes. Remember, if the price looks too good to be true, it probably is. In particular, be careful when purchasing high-tech goods, especially when prices are far below retail. Certain high-end items such as flat-panel displays, notebook computers, and cell phones are likely targets for scammers. In many cases, it's appropriate to ask for a serial number before sending payment.

  • Ask for sellers address and telephone number
    • Once you have negotiated the price and have decided to buy the item, ask for the seller's phone number and call him/her up at a random time to make sure he/she is receiving the calls. Honest sellers should be able to provide this information. Having a seller who has a registered telephone number at the other end, will make the seller more trackable and hence less likely to be a fraud.

  • Use a payment method with fraud protection
    • We highly advise AGAINST sending payment via wire transfer. Many fraudulent sellers only accept money by wire transfer, Money Gram, or bank transfer because buyers cannot get their money back and sellers cannot be tracked. If you are within the US and must pay by money order, we suggest using a postal money order. Postal money orders can be investigated, while other money orders cannot.

    There are many forms of payment that provide protection for buyers. Credit cards, escrow services such as Escrow.com, C.O.D. shipping, and online payment services, offer varying degrees of protection.

  • Track your shipment
    • Most major shipping companies allow people to track shipments while they are in transit. We recommended getting a tracking number from the seller, so you can monitor your item in transit. Make sure you are familiar with the seller's shipper, and be aware that there are fake shipping companies on the web which pretend to track a false shipment.

    If you feel a seller is acting fraudulently, please contact askht.com immediately at: abuse@OLX.com. Back to top


    What are the things that potentially fraudulent buyers do?

    • Ask you to wire money into their account.
    • Buyer offers high-value (but fake) cashier's check in exchange for your for sale item. The value of cashier's check often far exceeds your item and the buyer asks you to wire the balance via money transfer service. Banks will often cash these fake checks AND THEN HOLD YOU RESPONSIBLE WHEN THE CHECK FAILS TO CLEAR . Scam often involves a 3rd party (shipping agent, business associate owing buyer money). We would strongly discourage you from wiring money.
    • Recommend an unfamiliar escrow or payment service.
    • Place large orders to be sent to a foreign location.
    • Say they will pay you half of what's due before they receive the item, and half payment afterwards.
    • Will not provide you a verifiable telephone number.
    • Pay with an international credit card or cashier's check.
    Back to top


    What should I do if I suspect a fraudulent buyer?
    If you feel a buyer is acting fraudulently, please contact us at abuse@OLX.com. Back to top
